# Ensure all cleaned datasets exist
if "df_airport_cleaned" not in locals():
    print("Error: df_airport_cleaned is not defined. Please clean your airport dataset first.")

if "df_iata_icao_cleaned" not in locals():
    print("Error: df_iata_icao_cleaned is not defined. Please clean your IATA/ICAO dataset first.")

if "df_category_cleaned" not in locals():
    print("Error: df_category_cleaned is not defined. Please clean your category dataset first.")

if "df_subcategory_cleaned" not in locals():
    print("Error: df_subcategory_cleaned is not defined. Please clean your subcategory dataset first.")

# Merge complaints data with cleaned airport info
df_airport_merged = df_airport_cleaned.merge(df_iata_icao_cleaned, left_on="airport", right_on="iata", how="left")
df_category_merged = df_category_cleaned.merge(df_iata_icao_cleaned, left_on="airport", right_on="iata", how="left")
df_subcategory_merged = df_subcategory_cleaned.merge(df_iata_icao_cleaned, left_on="airport", right_on="iata", how="left")

# Convert year_month to datetime format
df_category_merged["year_month"] = pd.to_datetime(df_category_merged["year_month"])
df_airport_merged["year_month"] = pd.to_datetime(df_airport_merged["year_month"])
df_subcategory_merged["year_month"] = pd.to_datetime(df_subcategory_merged["year_month"])

# Confirm that merged datasets are available
print("\nCleaned and Merged Data Preview:")
print(df_airport_merged.head())

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Group and sort top 20 airports by complaint count
airport_complaints = df_airport_merged.groupby("airport_name")["count"].sum().reset_index()
airport_complaints = airport_complaints.sort_values(by="count", ascending=False).head(20)

# Create pivot table
pivot_data = airport_complaints.pivot_table(index="airport_name", values="count")

# Plot heatmap with correct annotations and color mapping
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 6))
ax = sns.heatmap(
    pivot_data,
    cmap="Reds",
    annot=True,         # Automatically annotate with count values
    fmt=",.0f",          # Format with thousands separator
    linewidths=0.5,
    cbar_kws={'label': 'Complaint Count'}
)

plt.title("Heat Map: Top 20 Airports with the Most TSA Complaints")
plt.xlabel("Complaint Count")
plt.ylabel("Airport")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

from prophet import Prophet
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# STEP 1: Prepare the data

# Aggregate complaints by month
df_trend = df_category_merged.groupby("year_month")["count"].sum().reset_index()

# Prophet expects columns named 'ds' (date) and 'y' (value)
df_trend.rename(columns={'year_month': 'ds', 'count': 'y'}, inplace=True)

# STEP 2: Initialize and fit the model
model = Prophet()
model.fit(df_trend)

# STEP 3: Create future dates for forecasting
# Forecast the next 12 months 
future = model.make_future_dataframe(periods=12, freq='ME')

# STEP 4: Make predictions
forecast = model.predict(future)

# STEP 5: Plot the forecast
fig1 = model.plot(forecast)
plt.title("Forecasted TSA Complaints")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Complaint Count")
plt.show()

# View the forecast data
forecast[['ds', 'yhat', 'yhat_lower', 'yhat_upper']].tail(12)
